Example 16: DUTERTE: FIGHT BACK, GET KILLED During the ICC Pre-Trial Chamber I confirmation of charges hearing on Thursday, former President Rodrigo Duterte’s lawyer, Atty. Nicholas Kaufman, claimed that the term “neutralization” referred only to police using lethal force in self-defense. Netizens, however, pointed to Duterte’s admission before the Senate Blue Ribbon Committee in 2024 that he ordered police to provoke drug suspects into fighting back so they could be killed. Duterte also identified former Philippine National Police chief Ronald “Bato” dela Rosa as one of the officers he directed to carry out these orders.